track_notes:
2.8 mile hike on the Bartram Trail with 900 elevation gain, with most of the elevation gain in the second half of the hike. The 0.1 mile spur trail to the summit is the only steep section. Summit has an open rocky area approximately 50X 25 surrounded by short trees.

The trailhead (35.076, -83.288) is located at the end of FS Road 4522 with parking for 5-10 vehicles. FS 4522 does not show up in Google Maps, but it starts at 35.080, -83.281 on Dendy Orchard Road.

There are a couple of short (0.3-0.4) spur trails that lead to other (non-SOTA) summits. Neither are really worth the effort for a side trip. There are better views along the trail. There is a nice outcrop about half way up Jones Knob. This is pretty close to the trailhead and would make a nice sunset stop if you time it right.
